<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Daniel Tarockoff — Special Projects</title>
  <meta name="description" content="A simple public website for Daniel Tarockoff's special projects, ideas, and experiments." />
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
  <meta property="og:title" content="Daniel Tarockoff — Special Projects" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="A simple public website for special projects, ideas, and experiments." />
  <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #0b0d10;
      --card: #13171c;
      --text: #f5f7fa;
      --muted: #b8c0cc;
      --line: #252c35;
      --accent: #8ec5ff;
      --accent-2: #c4f0d4;
      --max: 860px;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0b0d10 0%, #10151b 100%);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .wrap {
      width: min(calc(100% - 32px), var(--max));
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    header {
      padding: 72px 0 36px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .eyebrow {
      color: var(--accent-2);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4.8rem);
      line-height: 0.98;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    }

    .intro {
      margin-top: 20px;
      max-width: 700px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .nav {
      display: flex;
      gap: 18px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 28px;
    }

    .nav a {
      padding: 10px 14px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 999px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    main {
      padding: 36px 0 72px;
    }

    section {
      margin-top: 22px;
      padding: 28px;
      background: rgba(19, 23, 28, 0.8);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 20px;
      backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    }

    h2 {
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    p {
      margin: 10px 0 0;
    }

    .project {
      padding-top: 18px;
      margin-top: 18px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .project:first-of-type {
      margin-top: 0;
      padding-top: 0;
      border-top: 0;
    }

    .tag {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 8px;
      padding: 4px 10px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: #1b2330;
      color: #c9def8;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }

    footer {
      padding: 24px 0 60px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .small {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow">Special Projects</div>
      <h1>Daniel Tarockoff</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        A public home for projects, experiments, and ideas I'm building across technology, culture, consciousness, and creative work.
      </p>
      <nav class="nav" aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="#projects">Projects</a>
        <a href="#about">About</a>
        <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <div class="wrap">
      <section id="projects">
        <h2>Current Projects</h2>

        <div class="project">
          <h3>Project One</h3>
          <p>A short description of a special project you're working on. Keep it simple: what it is, why it matters, and what stage it's in.</p>
          <div class="tag">In Progress</div>
        </div>

        <div class="project">
          <h3>Project Two</h3>
          <p>A second project can live here. This page is intentionally lightweight so you can publish fast and update it later.</p>
          <div class="tag">Exploration</div>
        </div>

        <div class="project">
          <h3>Project Three</h3>
          <p>Add links here later to writeups, decks, essays, prototypes, or anything else you want people to discover.</p>
          <div class="tag">Coming Soon</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="about">
        <h2>About</h2>
        <p>
          I'm interested in building thoughtful, ambitious things at the intersection of human potential, technology, and culture.
        </p>
        <p class="small">
          This site will evolve over time. For now, it's a simple index of what I'm working on.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="contact">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Reach me at <a href="mailto:hello@example.com">hello@example.com</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="small">
          You can swap this for your real email, LinkedIn, X, or another public contact point.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="wrap">
      © <span id="year"></span> Daniel Tarockoff
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
    document.getElementById('year').textContent = new Date().getFullYear();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
